From Keith de Solla Subject CDN gun laws MODERATOR Nice summary Keith I talked to the federal of Justice DOJ Ottawa to try and clarify a bunch of things regarding changes to Canadian gun I am posting here for informational purposes questions to email followup to It is still technically feasible but almost impossible to get a concealed carry permit in This is contrary to what I was told by a police It is still legal to use lethal force such as a firearm to protect life also contrary to what the officer told Guns must be stored locked up and unloaded Regarding hi capacity magazines it is still not clear who will be exempt or how this will be This is up to each The general idea is that exempt persons will receive a letter form authorizing them to possess the high capacity Apparently the authorization is to specify how many of these 'prohibited weapons' you will be allowed to Dealers will be allowed to order high capacity mags for those allowed to possess them but will not be allowed to stock High capacity magazines converted to comply with the new limits will not be considered prohibited Amendments to the regulations specify some possible methods to alter the Some manufacturers Beretta will be marketing reduced capacity God knows how much they'll charge for these This covers most of what we I have typed this from memory do not take it as I am not a lawyer and I refuse to play one on Keith de Solla IPSC Ontario OHA NFA SFC OFAH Frontenac Rifle and Pistol Club